for once. It's keeping things a secret from the

isn't beautiful black and white images. Depression
is lonely and frustrating and mostly just fucking
exhausting."

When we say "the China man", we are referring to the

-We don't know what "small" and "large" mean. It's either a
"half" or "whole" order.
-Fried rice is not allowed to have a "lightskin" color to it. It is
brownskin or darker,

choice of meat.
-FRIED RICE DOES NOT CONTAIN PEAS OR CARROTS.
*Reread the previous statement to ensure understanding*
-You have two and ONY two drink options: Vess and Mystics.
-The red pepper is noticeably hotter than it should be.
-The Chinaman is more than likely to be in walking distance of a
liquor store, beauty supply store or check cashing/payday loan
spot. And in some cases....all three.
-A St. Paul sandwich (no I am not making up the name) is the
most awkwardly delicious food on this side of the Potomac River.
Shoutout to my guy Corey for enjoying this when he visits.
-I am unsure how you "braise" chicken, but the hot braised
chicken is a feat of culinary greatness.
They SAY it's crab meat in crab rangoon. But....whatever.
-Did I say that fried rice does not contain peas or carrots?
